<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Let&#39;s settle this debate once and for all. Bear in mind, this would apply to domestic cricket too. For example, if you banned T20, there won&#39;t be any domestic T20 leagues. </p> <p>&quot;But Dry-Supermarket7115 all three formats are beautiful in their own right&quot;. Yes, I know. But I&#39;ll be damned if you liked all 3 formats equally. You&#39;d be lying to yourself just like all the parents who claim to love all their children equally. </p> <p>Let&#39;s see which format is invaluable and which is (relatively) dispensable. The purpose of this exercise is to figure out what <a href="/r/cricket">r/cricket</a> truly likes about the sport and what it doesn&#39;t. Present strong arguments for your case.</p> <p>PS - T10 and The Hundred don&#39;t count.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Dry-Supermarket7115"> /u/Dry-Supermarket7115 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/w7q3py/gun_to_your_head_which_format_of_the_game_would/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/w7q3py/gun_to_your_head_which_format_of_the_game_would/">[comments]</a></span>